      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.On2ZrPJTe8FURsXY]{Operative Exploit}</p>\n<p>Whether you use smoke, holograms, or just a convincing lie, you can convince your enemy that they are surrounded, backing into a trap, or otherwise at risk from some unseen danger. As a move action, you can select a target within melee range. The target must succeed at a Will save or become @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.MZ8OoH1GE9qDMyCD]{Flat-Footed} until the end of their turn. If they fail the save, you can spend a Resolve Point to make them flat-footed until the end of your next turn instead.</p>"
